  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Mexico</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the project taking place in the state of Veracruz, in Mexico, is to promote active citizenship with focus on the citizen right of access to public information. The project analyses the mechanisms of citizen participation and promote various strategies of participation. Within the project committees of locals are founded to follow the activities of local governement and the state of Veracruz, and their work guided and supported. In addition to this citizen participation is encouraged through access to internet. The project has about 1000 direct beneficiaries, of which over 50% are indigenious.</narrative>
  </description>
